03:01:46.080 --> 03:01:49.750
OK, well [inaudible] OK,
I'll read it in whole.

03:01:49.750 --> 03:01:51.050
Thank you.

03:01:51.050 --> 03:01:53.610
It's called "The
Blighted Star Fruit":

03:01:53.610 --> 03:01:58.930
"To pass through astonishment
and know much too late.

03:01:58.930 --> 03:02:04.080
And because habit makes us
strange, I find myself searching

03:02:04.080 --> 03:02:08.010
on a landscape that generates
questions beyond its ability

03:02:08.010 --> 03:02:09.790
to solve.

03:02:09.790 --> 03:02:13.730
That dark post out there
might be this poem standing

03:02:13.730 --> 03:02:18.600
as you would?lead in the 4th
grade play??under theater lights

03:02:18.600 --> 03:02:22.090
and your shadows that
petal around you.

03:02:22.090 --> 03:02:25.410
And what should be
most memorable isn't.

03:02:25.410 --> 03:02:29.550
So, I recall those prolonged
moments of silence, incongruous.

03:02:29.550 --> 03:02:33.170
And revealing as
metaphor, most frequently.

03:02:33.170 --> 03:02:36.670
For instance, waiting
at the bus stop in Pai

03:02:36.670 --> 03:02:39.490
in a midmorning the hue
of the roadside guardrails

03:02:39.490 --> 03:02:42.600
that dot the cliff's
side like Morse code.

03:02:42.600 --> 03:02:47.030
Before leaving with trees, those
felled, ones half-painted white,

03:02:47.030 --> 03:02:51.370
the burnt trunks -- That passed
by like the so many phenomena

03:02:51.370 --> 03:02:54.390
of our days blurred
together into a motion.

03:02:54.390 --> 03:02:58.310
At times, convincing
as a nickelodeon's,

03:02:58.310 --> 03:02:59.980
I waited under the thatched roof

03:02:59.980 --> 03:03:02.830
of the station with
other travelers.

03:03:02.830 --> 03:03:05.150
With each in our
common solitude risen

03:03:05.150 --> 03:03:06.750
around like that Haydn piece.

03:03:06.750 --> 03:03:10.820
In the tunnel I descended into
on my way out onto Broadway

03:03:10.820 --> 03:03:15.220
from the 1 train some months
ago, it seemed of Hopper.

03:03:15.220 --> 03:03:20.440
Star fruit on the ground
discolored, withering, blighted.

03:03:20.440 --> 03:03:22.500
Three of the town's
strays hobbled

03:03:22.500 --> 03:03:25.080
by before midday's
heat stalled the town

03:03:25.080 --> 03:03:28.560
like some lost Stephano,
Trinculo, and their lamed,

03:03:28.560 --> 03:03:32.660
Dark sycophant?-- ?at least
that's what they were for me.

03:03:32.660 --> 03:03:36.910
It wasn't comfort, never
comfort, but something else.

03:03:36.910 --> 03:03:40.440
And when each moment with
expectations for more

03:03:40.440 --> 03:03:45.170
Than it can hold leads to the
next, and soon??as then --

03:03:45.170 --> 03:03:49.720
expectation fills up the day
as does your breath a balloon,

03:03:49.720 --> 03:03:54.050
the day floats with such
care and strange hours.

03:03:54.050 --> 03:03:57.770
And both pleasure and pain
are motions of the soul --

03:03:57.770 --> 03:04:03.770
plato wrote, ?poetry's
banisher, beauty's guard."

03:04:03.770 --> 03:04:09.230
Two. "My hands grow
differently used.

03:04:09.230 --> 03:04:10.940
While one hand thumbs pages,

03:04:10.940 --> 03:04:13.980
the other hand steadies
open the book.

03:04:13.980 --> 03:04:18.050
It's the other hand that rests
on the desk, forearm paralleled

03:04:18.050 --> 03:04:20.350
to the table's edge,
all the fingers,

03:04:20.350 --> 03:04:23.540
except the thumb
holding the blank field.

03:04:23.540 --> 03:04:28.430
One hand's mole a gnat flattened
between pinky and ring finger.

03:04:28.430 --> 03:04:30.640
The other hand's palm-side,

03:04:30.640 --> 03:04:33.390
below the skin enough it's
likely a splinter left

03:04:33.390 --> 03:04:35.320
for years.

03:04:35.320 --> 03:04:37.200
Just one hand fits my Discman,

03:04:37.200 --> 03:04:39.290
plugged in while
watching those around,

03:04:39.290 --> 03:04:42.880
no news-as-white-noise
here to occupy my sight.

03:04:42.880 --> 03:04:46.340
Kids who bus to school hours
away tooth picking slivers

03:04:46.340 --> 03:04:49.060
of chili-dappled
mango slices in.

03:04:49.060 --> 03:04:52.050
A triple-sweatered lady
palming back her hair

03:04:52.050 --> 03:04:57.270
in a thick Thai pre-dawn June;
the one foreigner other than us,

03:04:57.270 --> 03:05:01.280
earphone couched; and
her shape, dozed slack,

03:05:01.280 --> 03:05:05.440
coat-blanketed, neck
against my side.

03:05:05.440 --> 03:05:08.070
One hand rests.

03:05:08.070 --> 03:05:10.730
Half a day ago, under
a mosquito net,

03:05:10.730 --> 03:05:14.020
flushed with the desk fan
sitting on the rattan floor,

03:05:14.020 --> 03:05:16.070
one hand kept on the steady act

03:05:16.070 --> 03:05:19.410
of beckoning behind the
tongue-swelled clit,

03:05:19.410 --> 03:05:23.420
uncreasing the ridged roof,
almost like the mouth's roof

03:05:23.420 --> 03:05:25.630
as it slopes down toward teeth,

03:05:25.630 --> 03:05:29.220
like rubbing the dampened
cave wall, finger-darkened,

03:05:29.220 --> 03:05:32.580
as the guide turns
his back to us.

03:05:32.580 --> 03:05:34.780
The other hand traced
its crook?--

03:05:34.780 --> 03:05:38.370
that delta-creased pad set
between thumb and fingers,

03:05:38.370 --> 03:05:40.190
hand's most fleshy zone?

03:05:40.190 --> 03:05:41.940
-- ?on the torso.

03:05:41.940 --> 03:05:45.880
The other hand then stilled her
hip, mosquito net, weighted,

03:05:45.880 --> 03:05:49.600
walling out stitches of ants,
from its hook, a viscous drape

03:05:49.600 --> 03:05:52.530
like that through one
hand's two fingers.

03:05:52.530 --> 03:05:58.350
Oddly, only one hand drums along
the CD, Converge, Jane Doe,

03:05:58.350 --> 03:06:01.640
as the crowd would rupture
outward into a circle pit?--

03:06:01.640 --> 03:06:05.700
?a vortex in reverse --
if this were a concert.

03:06:05.700 --> 03:06:08.660
The other hand just
bides its time.

03:06:08.660 --> 03:06:12.100
Milton's clumsy other
hand, God's other hand

03:06:12.100 --> 03:06:15.880
that lessing chose, and that
Spaniard's other hand riddled

03:06:15.880 --> 03:06:19.180
useless at Lepanto,
a bullet lodged

03:06:19.180 --> 03:06:21.870
into that scurvied poet's chest,

03:06:21.870 --> 03:06:24.690
the other hand remembers
and betrays.

03:06:24.690 --> 03:06:29.220
The other hand cries out,
which was Keats's living one?

03:06:29.220 --> 03:06:30.870
Neither hand scarred yet,

03:06:30.870 --> 03:06:34.710
even after thumb-knuckle
tempted a sander in shop class,

03:06:34.710 --> 03:06:38.180
impulse from imagining too much.

03:06:38.180 --> 03:06:40.840
One hand's cushion
bears the pencil,

03:06:40.840 --> 03:06:43.920
my friend whose tasks are
split between his hands,

03:06:43.920 --> 03:06:48.430
"I eat with my left hand,
punch with the other"?--

03:06:48.430 --> 03:06:51.950
says we whack off with
the hand we write.

03:06:51.950 --> 03:06:54.690
Each hand on different
shaded denim thighs,

03:06:54.690 --> 03:06:59.130
The unclipped nails crude
halos of sun-blocking hills.

03:06:59.130 --> 03:07:04.050
One hand lets forth words;
the other hand holds it back."

03:07:04.050 --> 03:07:10.550
Three. Chased by a three-legged
dog to the temple stairs,

03:07:10.550 --> 03:07:13.940
past all the fallen star
fruit, the veined tips the last

03:07:13.940 --> 03:07:18.210
to wither, the through-light
flesh sun- and bug-eaten.

03:07:18.210 --> 03:07:21.410
We crossed paths with
a one-legged man?--

03:07:21.410 --> 03:07:24.820
?wordless sounds, in
that permanent wild gaze,

03:07:24.820 --> 03:07:28.030
crutching down the stairs, 400!

03:07:28.030 --> 03:07:31.450
As we stopped to catch
a break mid-flight.

03:07:31.450 --> 03:07:35.040
Our breath would last us a
run-through of the temple, and,

03:07:35.040 --> 03:07:39.540
in the first hallway?--
him?!, his phatic calls,

03:07:39.540 --> 03:07:43.520
tics and unwilled smile facing
the morning that just passed,

03:07:43.520 --> 03:07:47.150
the sun no longer in front of
his propped body, but above it,

03:07:47.150 --> 03:07:51.490
the valley overabundant with the
real light that stole our day.

03:07:51.490 --> 03:07:53.920
The fog too lifted
against my sight.

03:07:53.920 --> 03:07:55.220
We paused.

03:07:55.220 --> 03:07:57.910
Having just climbed the hill,
we agreed to leave our shoes

03:07:57.910 --> 03:08:00.120
on despite sandals
stationed on the stoop,

03:08:00.120 --> 03:08:03.080
and then we turned
towards that hall.

03:08:03.080 --> 03:08:06.460
-- Let's go -- he
ends, befriended,

03:08:06.460 --> 03:08:09.350
prayer Phaedrus-empty.

03:08:09.350 --> 03:08:13.320
?The driver gases the bus off
the parking brakes to idle back

03:08:13.320 --> 03:08:16.680
out the station; the attendants
scoop up the wood wedges

03:08:16.680 --> 03:08:18.620
and clatter the door shut.

03:08:18.620 --> 03:08:20.920
The passengers all shift.

03:08:20.920 --> 03:08:23.820
In the chapter among the
deformed and footless,

03:08:23.820 --> 03:08:26.860
Zhuangzi [phonetic] ends,
arguing for the greatest of men,

03:08:26.860 --> 03:08:30.980
a man void of feelings:
'The Way gave him a face,

03:08:30.980 --> 03:08:35.160
Heaven gave him a form,
can't you call him a man?'

03:08:35.160 --> 03:08:39.570
Yet there are things I
love: The sun, you, travel.

03:08:39.570 --> 03:08:42.750
And back again, the
thick fog parts us

03:08:42.750 --> 03:08:46.130
from the obliterating
Turner sun.

03:08:46.130 --> 03:08:48.610
Pretty soon, come
day, the motorbikes,

03:08:48.610 --> 03:08:51.340
The Rough Guide says, 'all
tourists should try will buzz

03:08:51.340 --> 03:08:54.150
by those three dogs',
all lethargic,

03:08:54.150 --> 03:08:56.860
the largest too tired
to dry-hump.

03:08:56.860 --> 03:09:00.310
His red tip unsheathing,
there's no neutering here.

03:09:00.310 --> 03:09:07.020
The black one, bald in spots,
wouldn't even fight it off.

03:09:07.020 --> 03:09:09.740
The mottled one coiled
back like the dog

03:09:09.740 --> 03:09:13.960
that badgers Bosch's wayfarer,
andaged, poor bastard,

03:09:13.960 --> 03:09:16.770
with his gnarled stick,
not looking at us,

03:09:16.770 --> 03:09:20.780
but rather caught looking back,
And above his head a doorway --

03:09:20.780 --> 03:09:24.550
?no, the gallows??-- The same
one Brueghel's final peasants

03:09:24.550 --> 03:09:26.560
romped beneath?

03:09:26.560 --> 03:09:28.650
My turn now to sleep.

03:09:28.650 --> 03:09:30.520
I can dab off from my jeans,

03:09:30.520 --> 03:09:33.680
your drool just reaching my
thigh as you do, with care,

03:09:33.680 --> 03:09:37.160
from our sheets when?-- yet
that stuff, all that stuff

03:09:37.160 --> 03:09:40.130
of ours still spots
our many beds

03:09:40.130 --> 03:09:44.180
with different aged salt-rings,
each gasp less a sound

03:09:44.180 --> 03:09:46.810
than a failure at silence.

03:09:46.810 --> 03:09:52.220
Before us another strange town,
while for others school, home,

03:09:52.220 --> 03:09:56.890
maybe work, a field,
someplace normal, there,

03:09:56.890 --> 03:10:00.940
someplace beyond sight
from its roadside stop.

03:10:00.940 --> 03:10:05.730
Abroad a month, toward a year
in another country, Anne?-- ?

03:10:05.730 --> 03:10:11.800
Anacrusis: these days I'm lost
in, reminded of my presence

03:10:11.800 --> 03:10:13.930
as if catching a stranger's wave

03:10:13.930 --> 03:10:18.510
to the yet-to-be-seen
man behind you as yours."

